Jeanette Chabalala Eight people, including five children, were killed after a fire broke out in the Taiwan informal settlement in Khayelitsha. The incident happened just after 01:30 on Monday morning, City of Cape Town fire and rescue services spokesperson Theo Layne said. Layne said four informal structures were destroyed by the fire which left 22 people displaced. The cause of the fire was unknown. The matter has been handed to the police for further investigations, he said. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter * This story has been updated to reflect that police now say five of the dead were children and not four. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  